{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881038875,"sessionID":"ses_285417fa2ffekbstOpE1YTRYXg","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac22b63001XuiUKsj82yX5Q1","messageID":"msg_d7abedcbe001ti17qKKTo0FC5H","sessionID":"ses_285417fa2ffekbstOpE1YTRYXg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f0ea1c8c9a1d4a3b831adf77ba1a6ab4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nHelm Chart for AgentCube platform provides a standardized, configurable, and reusable Kubernetes deployment solution. The chart encapsulates all necessary Kubernetes resources (CRDs, Deployments, Services, ConfigMaps, RBAC) and enables flexible configuration through Values files, simplifying deployment across multiple environments.\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML + Go Templates  \n**Source Root:** `manifests/charts/agentcube/`  \n**Size:** L\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Chart Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata\n├── values.yaml                         # Default configuration\n├── values-dev.yaml                     # Development environment overrides\n├── values-prod.yaml                    # Production environment overrides\n├── values-test.yaml                    # Test environment overrides\n├── templates/\n│   ├── crds/\n│   │   ├── agentruntime.yaml           # AgentRuntime CRD\n│   │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml        # CodeInterpreter CRD\n│   ├── controller-manager/\n│   │   ├── deployment.yaml             # Controller Manager deployment\n│   │   ├── service.yaml                # Controller Manager service\n│   │   ├── serviceaccount.yaml         # Controller Manager service account\n│   │   └── rbac.yaml                   # Controller Manager RBAC rules\n│   ├── workload-manager/\n│   │   ├── deployment.yaml             # Workload Manager deployment\n│   │   ├── service.yaml                # Workload Manager service\n│   │   ├── serviceaccount.yaml         # Workload Manager service account\n│   │   └── rbac.yaml                   # Workload Manager RBAC rules\n│   ├── router/\n│   │   ├── deployment.yaml             # Router deployment\n│   │   ├── service.yaml                # Router service\n│   │   ├── serviceaccount.yaml         # Router service account\n│   │   └── rbac.yaml                   # Router RBAC rules\n│   ├── rbac/\n│   │   ├── clusterrole.yaml            # Cluster-wide role\n│   │   └── clusterrolebinding.yaml     # Cluster-wide role binding\n│   ├── monitoring/\n│   │   └── servicemonitor.yaml         # Prometheus ServiceMonitor\n│   ├── configmaps/\n│   │   └── config.yaml                 # Application configuration\n│   ├── secrets/\n│   │   └── secret.yaml                 # Sensitive configuration\n│   ├── networkpolicies/\n│   │   └── networkpolicy.yaml          # Network access control\n│   ├── poddisruptionbudgets/\n│   │   ├── controller-manager.yaml\n│   │   ├── workload-manager.yaml\n│   │   └── router.yaml\n│   ├── NOTES.txt                       # Installation notes\n│   ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helpers\n│   └── ingress.yaml                    # Ingress configuration\n├── tests/\n│   ├── controller-manager_test.yaml\n│   ├── workload-manager_test.yaml\n│   └── router_test.yaml\n└── README.md                           # Chart documentation\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Helm Chart                             │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐     │\n│  │   CRDs       │  │  Controller  │  │   Workload   │     │\n│  │              │  │   Manager    │  │   Manager    │     │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘     │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐     │\n│  │    Router    │  │    RBAC      │  │  Monitoring  │     │\n│  │              │  │              │  │              │     │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              │ helm install/upgrade\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   Kubernetes Cluster                        │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │              API Server + etcd                       │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐     │\n│  │  Controller  │  │   Workload   │  │    Router    │     │\n│  │   Manager    │  │   Manager    │  │              │     │\n│  │   (Pods)     │  │   (Pods)     │  │   (Pods)     │     │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘     │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐     │\n│  │   Services   │  │     CRDs     │  │   Secrets/   │     │\n│  │              │  │              │  │  ConfigMaps  │     │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Chart.yaml\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v2\nname: agentcube\ndescription: Helm chart for AgentCube platform - Kubernetes-native AI agent runtime and code interpreter\ntype: application\nversion: 1.0.0\nappVersion: \"1.0.0\"\nkeywords:\n  - agentcube\n  - ai\n  - code-interpreter\n  - agent-runtime\n  - kubernetes\nmaintainers:\n  - name: AgentCube Team\n    email: team@agentcube.io\nhome: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\nsources:\n  - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\nicon: https://agentcube.io/logo.svg\nannotations:\n  artifacthub.io/category: ai-machine-learning\n  artifacthub.io/license: Apache-2.0\n  artifacthub.io/operator: \"false\"\n```\n\n### Values.yaml Hierarchy\n\n```yaml\n# Global configuration applied to all components\nglobal:\n  imageRegistry: docker.io\n  imagePullSecrets: []\n  namespaceOverride: agentcube\n  labels: {}\n  annotations: {}\n\n# Image pull policy for all components\nimagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n\n# Controller Manager configuration\ncontrollerManager:\n  enabled: true\n  replicaCount: 2\n  image:\n    repository: agentcube/controller-manager\n    tag: v1.0.0\n    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n  service:\n    type: ClusterIP\n    port: 8080\n    targetPort: 8080\n    annotations: {}\n  resources:\n    requests:\n      cpu: 100m\n      memory: 128Mi\n    limits:\n      cpu: 500m\n      memory: 512Mi\n  nodeSelector: {}\n  tolerations: []\n  affinity: {}\n  podAnnotations: {}\n  podLabels: {}\n  securityContext:\n    runAsNonRoot: true\n    runAsUser: 1000\n    fsGroup: 1000\n  containerSecurityContext:\n    allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n    capabilities:\n      drop:\n        - ALL\n    readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n  livenessProbe:\n    httpGet:\n      path: /healthz\n      port: 8080\n    initialDelaySeconds: 30\n    periodSeconds: 10\n    timeoutSeconds: 5\n    failureThreshold: 3\n    successThreshold: 1\n  readinessProbe:\n    httpGet:\n      path: /readyz\n      port: 8080\n    initialDelaySeconds: 10\n    periodSeconds: 5\n    timeoutSeconds: 3\n    failureThreshold: 3\n    successThreshold: 1\n  autoscaling:\n    enabled: false\n    minReplicas: 2\n    maxReplicas: 5\n    targetCPUUtilizationPercentage: 80\n    targetMemoryUtilizationPercentage: 80\n  podDisruptionBudget:\n    enabled: true\n    minAvailable: 1\n  env: []\n  envFrom: []\n  extraVolumeMounts: []\n  extraVolumes: []\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: true\n    name: \"\"\n    annotations: {}\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n    rules: []\n\n# Workload Manager configuration\nworkloadManager:\n  enabled: true\n  replicaCount: 2\n  image:\n    repository: agentcube/workload-manager\n    tag: v1.0.0\n    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n  service:\n    type: ClusterIP\n    port: 8080\n    targetPort: 8080\n    annotations: {}\n  resources:\n    requests:\n      cpu: 200m\n      memory: 256Mi\n    limits:\n      cpu: 1000m\n      memory: 1Gi\n  nodeSelector: {}\n  tolerations: []\n  affinity: {}\n  podAnnotations: {}\n  podLabels: {}\n  securityContext:\n    runAsNonRoot: true\n    runAsUser: 1000\n    fsGroup: 1000\n  containerSecurityContext:\n    allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n    capabilities:\n      drop:\n        - ALL\n    readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n  livenessProbe:\n    httpGet:\n      path: /healthz\n      port: 8080\n    initialDelaySeconds: 30\n    periodSeconds: 10\n    timeoutSeconds: 5\n    failureThreshold: 3\n  readinessProbe:\n    httpGet:\n      path: /readyz\n      port: 8080\n    initialDelaySeconds: 10\n    periodSeconds: 5\n    timeoutSeconds: 3\n    failureThreshold: 3\n  autoscaling:\n    enabled: false\n    minReplicas: 2\n    maxReplicas: 10\n    targetCPUUtilizationPercentage: 75\n    targetMemoryUtilizationPercentage: 80\n  podDisruptionBudget:\n    enabled: true\n    minAvailable: 1\n  env: []\n  envFrom: []\n  extraVolumeMounts: []\n  extraVolumes: []\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: true\n    name: \"\"\n    annotations: {}\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n    rules: []\n\n# Router configuration\nrouter:\n  enabled: true\n  replicaCount: 3\n  image:\n    repository: agentcube/router\n    tag: v1.0.0\n    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n  service:\n    type: ClusterIP\n    port: 8080\n    targetPort: 8080\n    annotations: {}\n    loadBalancerSourceRanges: []\n  ingress:\n    enabled: false\n    className: nginx\n    annotations: {}\n    hosts:\n      - host: agentcube.example.com\n        paths:\n          - path: /\n            pathType: Prefix\n    tls:\n      - secretName: agentcube-tls\n        hosts:\n          - agentcube.example.com\n  resources:\n    requests:\n      cpu: 150m\n      memory: 192Mi\n    limits:\n      cpu: 750m\n      memory: 768Mi\n  nodeSelector: {}\n  tolerations: []\n  affinity:\n    podAntiAffinity:\n      requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:\n      - labelSelector:\n          matchLabels:\n            app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n        topologyKey: kubernetes.io/hostname\n  podAnnotations: {}\n  podLabels: {}\n  securityContext:\n    runAsNonRoot: true\n    runAsUser: 1000\n    fsGroup: 1000\n  containerSecurityContext:\n    allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n    capabilities:\n      drop:\n        - ALL\n    readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n  livenessProbe:\n    httpGet:\n      path: /healthz\n      port: 8080\n    initialDelaySeconds: 30\n    periodSeconds: 10\n    timeoutSeconds: 5\n    failureThreshold: 3\n  readinessProbe:\n    httpGet:\n      path: /readyz\n      port: 8080\n    initialDelaySeconds: 10\n    periodSeconds: 5\n    timeoutSeconds: 3\n    failureThreshold: 3\n  autoscaling:\n    enabled: false\n    minReplicas: 3\n    maxReplicas: 10\n    targetCPUUtilizationPercentage: 70\n    targetMemoryUtilizationPercentage: 75\n  podDisruptionBudget:\n    enabled: true\n    minAvailable: 2\n  env: []\n  envFrom: []\n  extraVolumeMounts: []\n  extraVolumes: []\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: true\n    name: \"\"\n    annotations: {}\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n    rules: []\n\n# Global RBAC configuration\nrbac:\n  create: true\n  clusterRole:\n    create: true\n    rules:\n    - apiGroups:\n      - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n      resources:\n      - agentruntimes\n      - codeinterpreters\n      verbs:\n      - get\n      - list\n      - watch\n      - create\n      - update\n      - patch\n      - delete\n    - apiGroups:\n      - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n      resources:\n      - agentruntimes/status\n      - codeinterpreters/status\n      verbs:\n      - get\n      - update\n      - patch\n    - apiGroups:\n      - \"\"\n      resources:\n      - pods\n      - services\n      - configmaps\n      - secrets\n      verbs:\n      - get\n      - list\n      - watch\n      - create\n      - update\n      - patch\n      - delete\n    - apiGroups:\n      - \"\"\n      resources:\n      - pods/status\n      verbs:\n      - get\n    - apiGroups:\n      - \"\"\n      resources:\n      - events\n      verbs:\n      - create\n      - patch\n\n# Monitoring configuration\nmonitoring:\n  enabled: false\n  serviceMonitor:\n    enabled: false\n    interval: 30s\n    scrapeTimeout: 10s\n    labels:\n      release: prometheus\n    annotations: {}\n    metricRelabelings: []\n    relabelings: []\n  prometheusRule:\n    enabled: false\n    labels:\n      release: prometheus\n    rules: []\n\n# ConfigMaps configuration\nconfigMaps:\n  agentcubeConfig:\n    create: true\n    data:\n      LOG_LEVEL: info\n      LOG_FORMAT: json\n      METRICS_ENABLED: \"true\"\n      METRICS_PORT: \"9090\"\n      TRACING_ENABLED: \"false\"\n      TRACING_ENDPOINT: \"\"\n\n# Secrets configuration\nsecrets:\n  create: false\n  name: agentcube-secrets\n  data: {}\n\n# NetworkPolicies configuration\nnetworkPolicies:\n  enabled: false\n  defaultDeny: false\n  allowExternal: true\n  rules:\n    controllerManager:\n      ingress:\n      - from:\n        - podSelector:\n            matchLabels:\n              app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n        ports:\n        - port: 8080\n          protocol: TCP\n      egress:\n      - to:\n        - namespaceSelector: {}\n        ports:\n        - port: 443\n          protocol: TCP\n    workloadManager:\n      ingress:\n      - from:\n        - podSelector:\n            matchLabels:\n              app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n        ports:\n        - port: 8080\n          protocol: TCP\n      egress:\n      - to:\n        - namespaceSelector: {}\n        ports:\n        - port: 443\n          protocol: TCP\n    router:\n      ingress:\n      - from:\n        - namespaceSelector: {}\n        ports:\n        - port: 8080\n          protocol: TCP\n      egress:\n      - to:\n        - podSelector:\n            matchLabels:\n              app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n        ports:\n        - port: 8080\n          protocol: TCP\n\n# Ingress configuration\ningress:\n  enabled: false\n  className: nginx\n  annotations:\n    cert-manager.io/cluster-issuer: letsencrypt-prod\n  hosts:\n    - host: agentcube.example.com\n      paths:\n        - path: /\n          pathType: Prefix\n          backend:\n            service:\n              name: router\n              port:\n                number: 8080\n  tls:\n    - secretName: agentcube-tls\n      hosts:\n        - agentcube.example.com\n\n# Pod priority and preemption\npriorityClassName: \"\"\n\n# Extra manifests to include\nextraManifests: []\n\n# Post-install, pre-upgrade, post-upgrade hooks\nhooks:\n  preInstall:\n    enabled: false\n    image: busybox:latest\n    command: []\n  postInstall:\n    enabled: false\n    image: busybox:latest\n    command: []\n  preUpgrade:\n    enabled: false\n    image: busybox:latest\n    command: []\n  postUpgrade:\n    enabled: false\n    image: busybox:latest\n    command: []\n```\n\n### Helper Templates (_helpers.tpl)\n\n```yaml\n{{/*\nExpand the name of the chart.\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.name\" -}}\n{{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nCreate a default fully qualified app name.\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.fullname\" -}}\n{{- if .Values.fullnameOverride }}\n{{- .Values.fullnameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- $name := default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride }}\n{{- if contains $name .Release.Name }}\n{{- .Release.Name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- printf \"%s-%s\" .Release.Name $name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nCreate chart name and version as used by the chart label.\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.chart\" -}}\n{{- printf \"%s-%s\" .Chart.Name .Chart.Version | replace \"+\" \"_\" | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nCommon labels\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.labels\" -}}\nhelm.sh/chart: {{ include \"agentcube.chart\" . }}\n{{ include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . }}\n{{- if .Chart.AppVersion }}\napp.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion | quote }}\n{{- end }}\napp.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nSelector labels\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" -}}\napp.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\napp.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nCreate the name of the service account to use\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n{{- if .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n{{- default (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- default \"default\" .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nCreate the name of the service account to use\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n{{- if .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n{{- default (printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- default \"default\" .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nCreate the name of the service account to use\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n{{- if .Values.router.serviceAccount.create }}\n{{- default (printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) .Values.router.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- default \"default\" .Values.router.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nImage registry helper\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.imageRegistry\" -}}\n{{- .Values.global.imageRegistry | default \"\" -}}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{/*\nBuild fully qualified image reference\n*/}}\n{{- define \"agentcube.image\" -}}\n{{- $registry := include \"agentcube.imageRegistry\" . -}}\n{{- if $registry }}\n{{- printf \"%s/%s:%s\" $registry .repository .tag }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- printf \"%s:%s\" .repository .tag }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Template: CRD Installation\n\n**File:** `templates/crds/agentruntime.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\napiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\nkind: CustomResourceDefinition\nmetadata:\n  name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n  annotations:\n    helm.sh/hook: crd-install\n    helm.sh/hook-weight: \"-5\"\n    helm.sh/hook-delete-policy: before-hook-creation\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\nspec:\n  group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n  names:\n    kind: AgentRuntime\n    listKind: AgentRuntimeList\n    plural: agentruntimes\n    shortNames:\n    - art\n    singular: agentruntime\n  scope: Namespaced\n  versions:\n  - name: v1alpha1\n    served: true\n    storage: true\n    schema:\n      openAPIV3Schema:\n        type: object\n        properties:\n          apiVersion:\n            type: string\n          kind:\n            type: string\n          metadata:\n            type: object\n          spec:\n            type: object\n            properties:\n              maxSessionDuration:\n                type: string\n                default: \"8h\"\n              sessionTimeout:\n                type: string\n                default: \"15m\"\n              podTemplate:\n                type: object\n                properties:\n                  metadata:\n                    type: object\n                  spec:\n                    type: object\n              targetPort:\n                type: array\n                items:\n                  type: object\n                  properties:\n                    port:\n                      type: integer\n                      format: int32\n                    protocol:\n                      type: string\n                      enum: [\"HTTP\", \"HTTPS\"]\n                    pathPrefix:\n                      type: string\n                    name:\n                      type: string\n                required: [\"port\", \"protocol\"]\n            required: [\"maxSessionDuration\", \"sessionTimeout\", \"podTemplate\", \"targetPort\"]\n          status:\n            type: object\n            properties:\n              conditions:\n                type: array\n                items:\n                  type: object\n                  properties:\n                    lastTransitionTime:\n                      format: date-time\n                      type: string\n                    message:\n                      type: string\n                    reason:\n                      type: string\n                    status:\n                      type: string\n                    type:\n                      type: string\n                    observedGeneration:\n                      format: int64\n                      type: integer\n              observedGeneration:\n                format: int64\n                type: integer\n    subresources:\n      status: {}\n    additionalPrinterColumns:\n    - name: Age\n      type: date\n      jsonPath: .metadata.creationTimestamp\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: Controller Manager Deployment\n\n**File:** `templates/controller-manager/deployment.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\nspec:\n  replicas: {{ .Values.controllerManager.replicaCount }}\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n      app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      annotations:\n        checksum/config: {{ include (print $.Template.BasePath \"/configmaps/config.yaml\") . | sha256sum }}\n        {{- with .Values.controllerManager.podAnnotations }}\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n        {{- end }}\n      labels:\n        {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n        app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n        {{- with .Values.controllerManager.podLabels }}\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n        {{- end }}\n    spec:\n      {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n      imagePullSecrets:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      serviceAccountName: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n      securityContext:\n        {{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.securityContext | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- with .Values.controllerManager.nodeSelector }}\n      nodeSelector:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.controllerManager.affinity }}\n      affinity:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.controllerManager.tolerations }}\n      tolerations:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- if .Values.priorityClassName }}\n      priorityClassName: {{ .Values.priorityClassName }}\n      {{- end }}\n      containers:\n      - name: controller-manager\n        securityContext:\n          {{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.containerSecurityContext | nindent 10 }}\n        image: \"{{ include \"agentcube.image\" (dict \"registry\" .Values.global.imageRegistry \"repository\" .Values.controllerManager.image.repository \"tag\" .Values.controllerManager.image.tag) }}\"\n        imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.controllerManager.image.pullPolicy }}\n        args:\n        - --leader-elect\n        - --health-probe-bind-address=:8080\n        - --metrics-bind-address=:9090\n        ports:\n        - name: http\n          containerPort: 8080\n          protocol: TCP\n        - name: metrics\n          containerPort: 9090\n          protocol: TCP\n        {{- with .Values.controllerManager.livenessProbe }}\n        livenessProbe:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.controllerManager.readinessProbe }}\n        readinessProbe:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        resources:\n          {{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.resources | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- with .Values.controllerManager.env }}\n        env:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.controllerManager.envFrom }}\n        envFrom:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.controllerManager.extraVolumeMounts }}\n        volumeMounts:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.controllerManager.extraVolumes }}\n      volumes:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n      {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: Controller Manager Service\n\n**File:** `templates/controller-manager/service.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n  {{- with .Values.controllerManager.service.annotations }}\n  annotations:\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n  {{- end }}\nspec:\n  type: {{ .Values.controllerManager.service.type }}\n  ports:\n  - port: {{ .Values.controllerManager.service.port }}\n    targetPort: http\n    protocol: TCP\n    name: http\n  selector:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: Controller Manager ServiceAccount\n\n**File:** `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n  {{- with .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n  annotations:\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n  {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: Controller Manager RBAC\n\n**File:** `templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.rbac.create }}\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\nrules:\n{{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules | nindent 0 }}\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: Role\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: Workload Manager Deployment\n\n**File:** `templates/workload-manager/deployment.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.workloadManager.enabled }}\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\nspec:\n  replicas: {{ .Values.workloadManager.replicaCount }}\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n      app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      annotations:\n        checksum/config: {{ include (print $.Template.BasePath \"/configmaps/config.yaml\") . | sha256sum }}\n        {{- with .Values.workloadManager.podAnnotations }}\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n        {{- end }}\n      labels:\n        {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n        app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n        {{- with .Values.workloadManager.podLabels }}\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n        {{- end }}\n    spec:\n      {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n      imagePullSecrets:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      serviceAccountName: {{ include \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n      securityContext:\n        {{- toYaml .Values.workloadManager.securityContext | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- with .Values.workloadManager.nodeSelector }}\n      nodeSelector:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.workloadManager.affinity }}\n      affinity:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.workloadManager.tolerations }}\n      tolerations:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- if .Values.priorityClassName }}\n      priorityClassName: {{ .Values.priorityClassName }}\n      {{- end }}\n      containers:\n      - name: workload-manager\n        securityContext:\n          {{- toYaml .Values.workloadManager.containerSecurityContext | nindent 10 }}\n        image: \"{{ include \"agentcube.image\" (dict \"registry\" .Values.global.imageRegistry \"repository\" .Values.workloadManager.image.repository \"tag\" .Values.workloadManager.image.tag) }}\"\n        imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadManager.image.pullPolicy }}\n        args:\n        - --leader-elect\n        - --health-probe-bind-address=:8080\n        - --metrics-bind-address=:9090\n        ports:\n        - name: http\n          containerPort: 8080\n          protocol: TCP\n        - name: metrics\n          containerPort: 9090\n          protocol: TCP\n        {{- with .Values.workloadManager.livenessProbe }}\n        livenessProbe:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.workloadManager.readinessProbe }}\n        readinessProbe:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        resources:\n          {{- toYaml .Values.workloadManager.resources | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- with .Values.workloadManager.env }}\n        env:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.workloadManager.envFrom }}\n        envFrom:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.workloadManager.extraVolumeMounts }}\n        volumeMounts:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.workloadManager.extraVolumes }}\n      volumes:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n      {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: Router Deployment\n\n**File:** `templates/router/deployment.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.router.enabled }}\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: router\nspec:\n  replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicaCount }}\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n      app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      annotations:\n        checksum/config: {{ include (print $.Template.BasePath \"/configmaps/config.yaml\") . | sha256sum }}\n        {{- with .Values.router.podAnnotations }}\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n        {{- end }}\n      labels:\n        {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n        app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n        {{- with .Values.router.podLabels }}\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n        {{- end }}\n    spec:\n      {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n      imagePullSecrets:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      serviceAccountName: {{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n      securityContext:\n        {{- toYaml .Values.router.securityContext | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- with .Values.router.nodeSelector }}\n      nodeSelector:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.router.affinity }}\n      affinity:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.router.tolerations }}\n      tolerations:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n      {{- end }}\n      {{- if .Values.priorityClassName }}\n      priorityClassName: {{ .Values.priorityClassName }}\n      {{- end }}\n      containers:\n      - name: router\n        securityContext:\n          {{- toYaml .Values.router.containerSecurityContext | nindent 10 }}\n        image: \"{{ include \"agentcube.image\" (dict \"registry\" .Values.global.imageRegistry \"repository\" .Values.router.image.repository \"tag\" .Values.router.image.tag) }}\"\n        imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n        args:\n        - --leader-elect\n        - --health-probe-bind-address=:8080\n        - --metrics-bind-address=:9090\n        ports:\n        - name: http\n          containerPort: 8080\n          protocol: TCP\n        - name: metrics\n          containerPort: 9090\n          protocol: TCP\n        {{- with .Values.router.livenessProbe }}\n        livenessProbe:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.router.readinessProbe }}\n        readinessProbe:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        resources:\n          {{- toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- with .Values.router.env }}\n        env:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.router.envFrom }}\n        envFrom:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n        {{- with .Values.router.extraVolumeMounts }}\n        volumeMounts:\n          {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n        {{- end }}\n      {{- with .Values.router.extraVolumes }}\n      volumes:\n        {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n      {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: ServiceMonitor\n\n**File:** `templates/monitoring/servicemonitor.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.monitoring.enabled .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.enabled }}\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: ServiceMonitor\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    {{- with .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.labels }}\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n    {{- end }}\n  {{- with .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.annotations }}\n  annotations:\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n  {{- end }}\nspec:\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n  namespaceSelector:\n    matchNames:\n      - {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  endpoints:\n  - port: metrics\n    interval: {{ .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.interval }}\n    scrapeTimeout: {{ .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.scrapeTimeout }}\n    path: /metrics\n    {{- with .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.metricRelabelings }}\n    metricRelabelings:\n      {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n    {{- end }}\n    {{- with .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.relabelings }}\n    relabelings:\n      {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n    {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: PodDisruptionBudget\n\n**File:** `templates/poddisruptionbudgets/controller-manager.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.podDisruptionBudget.enabled }}\napiVersion: policy/v1\nkind: PodDisruptionBudget\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\nspec:\n  minAvailable: {{ .Values.controllerManager.podDisruptionBudget.minAvailable }}\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n      app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: Ingress\n\n**File:** `templates/ingress.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.ingress.enabled }}\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Ingress\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n  {{- with .Values.ingress.annotations }}\n  annotations:\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n  {{- end }}\nspec:\n  ingressClassName: {{ .Values.ingress.className }}\n  {{- if .Values.ingress.tls }}\n  tls:\n    {{- range .Values.ingress.tls }}\n    - hosts:\n        {{- range .hosts }}\n        - {{ . | quote }}\n        {{- end }}\n      secretName: {{ .secretName }}\n    {{- end }}\n  {{- end }}\n  rules:\n    {{- range .Values.ingress.hosts }}\n    - host: {{ .host | quote }}\n      http:\n        paths:\n          {{- range .paths }}\n          - path: {{ .path }}\n            pathType: {{ .pathType }}\n            backend:\n              service:\n                name: {{ .backend.service.name | default (printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" $)) }}\n                port:\n                  number: {{ .backend.service.port.number | default 8080 }}\n          {{- end }}\n    {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: NetworkPolicy\n\n**File:** `templates/networkpolicies/networkpolicy.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.networkPolicies.enabled }}\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\nspec:\n  podSelector: {}\n  {{- if .Values.networkPolicies.defaultDeny }}\n  policyTypes:\n  - Ingress\n  - Egress\n  {{- end }}\n  ingress:\n  {{- range .Values.networkPolicies.rules.controllerManager.ingress }}\n  - from:\n    {{- range .from }}\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n    {{- end }}\n    ports:\n    {{- range .ports }}\n    - {{ toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n    {{- end }}\n  {{- end }}\n  egress:\n  {{- range .Values.networkPolicies.rules.controllerManager.egress }}\n  - to:\n    {{- range .to }}\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n    {{- end }}\n    ports:\n    {{- range .ports }}\n    - {{ toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n    {{- end }}\n  {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: ConfigMap\n\n**File:** `templates/configmaps/config.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.configMaps.agentcubeConfig.create }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}-config\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\ndata:\n  {{- toYaml .Values.configMaps.agentcubeConfig.data | nindent 2 }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: Secret\n\n**File:** `templates/secrets/secret.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if .Values.secrets.create }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Secret\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.secrets.name | default (printf \"%s-secrets\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\ntype: Opaque\ndata:\n  {{- range $key, $value := .Values.secrets.data }}\n  {{ $key }}: {{ $value | b64enc }}\n  {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n### Template: NOTES.txt\n\n**File:** `templates/NOTES.txt`\n\n```yaml\nThank you for installing {{ .Chart.Name }}!\n\nYour release is named {{ .Release.Name }}.\n\nTo learn more about the release, try:\n\n  $ helm status {{ .Release.Name }}\n  $ helm get all {{ .Release.Name }}\n\n{{- if .Values.ingress.enabled }}\nTo access the AgentCube Router:\n\n  {{- range .Values.ingress.hosts }}\n  http{{ if $.Values.ingress.tls }}s{{ end }}://{{ .host }}\n  {{- end }}\n\n{{- else if contains \"NodePort\" .Values.router.service.type }}\n\nGet the Router URL by running these commands:\n\n  export NODE_PORT=$(kubectl get --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.ports[0].nodePort}\" services {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }})\n  export NODE_IP=$(kubectl get nodes --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} -o jsonpath=\"{.items[0].status.addresses[0].address}\")\n\n  echo http://$NODE_IP:$NODE_PORT\n\n{{- else if contains \"LoadBalancer\" .Values.router.service.type }}\n\nGet the Router URL by running these commands:\n\n  NOTE: It may take a few minutes for the LoadBalancer IP to be available.\n        You can watch the status by running 'kubectl get svc --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} -w {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}'\n\n  export SERVICE_IP=$(kubectl get svc --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }} -o jsonpath='{.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].ip}')\n\n  echo http://$SERVICE_IP:{{ .Values.router.service.port }}\n\n{{- else if contains \"ClusterIP\" .Values.router.service.type }}\n\nGet the Router URL by running these commands:\n\n  export POD_NAME=$(kubectl get pods --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} -l \"app.kubernetes.io/name={{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }},app.kubernetes.io/instance={{ .Release.Name }},app.kubernetes.io/component=router\" -o jsonpath=\"{.items[0].metadata.name}\")\n\n  kubectl port-forward --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} $POD_NAME 8080:8080\n\n  echo \"Visit http://127.0.0.1:8080 to use the AgentCube Router\"\n\n{{- end }}\n\n{{- if .Values.monitoring.enabled }}\n\nMonitoring is enabled. ServiceMonitor {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }} has been created.\n\nTo verify Prometheus is scraping metrics:\n\n  $ kubectl get servicemonitor {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }} -n {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n\n{{- end }}\n\nFor more information, visit:\n  https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Helm Template Validation\n\n**Linting:**\n```bash\nhelm lint ./agentcube\n```\n\n**Template rendering validation:**\n```bash\nhelm template agentcube ./agentcube --debug\n```\n\n**Values validation:**\n```bash\nhelm show values ./agentcube > values.yaml\n# Validate values.yaml manually or with schema validation tool\n```\n\n### Common Template Errors\n\n| Error Type | Cause | Resolution |\n|------------|-------|------------|\n| `variable not defined` | Reference to undefined template variable | Ensure variable is defined in _helpers.tpl or passed as parameter |\n| `invalid type for index` | Trying to index non-map/slice type | Check value type before indexing |\n| `nil pointer dereference` | Accessing field of nil value | Use `with` or `if` to check for nil |\n| `unexpected end` | Unclosed template block | Check for matching `{{-` and `}}` |\n| `redefinition` | Duplicate template definition | Ensure each template has unique name |\n| `unknown identifier` | Reference to unknown Go template function | Use available Helm template functions only |\n\n### Values Validation Errors\n\n| Error | Condition | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Invalid port | Port outside 1-65535 range | \"Port must be between 1 and 65535\" |\n| Invalid replica count | Replica count < 0 | \"Replica count must be non-negative\" |\n| Missing required value | Required field not set | \"Required value 'X' not set\" |\n| Invalid image tag | Empty image tag with tag required | \"Image tag cannot be empty\" |\n| Invalid resource request | CPU/memory request > limit | \"Resource request cannot exceed limit\" |\n\n### Installation/Upgrade Errors\n\n```bash\n# Error: CRD already exists with different schema\nSolution: helm upgrade --install --force or manually delete CRD\n\n# Error: Namespace does not exist\nSolution: kubectl create namespace <namespace>\n\n# Error: Image pull failure\nSolution: Check imagePullSecrets and image registry access\n\n# Error: Insufficient resources\nSolution: Adjust resource requests/limits in values.yaml\n\n# Error: RBAC permissions denied\nSolution: Ensure cluster-admin role or create necessary RBAC\n```\n\n### Rollback Strategy\n\n```bash\n# View revision history\nhelm history <release-name>\n\n# Rollback to previous version\nhelm rollback <release-name> <revision>\n\n# Rollback with specific values\nhelm rollback <release-name> <revision> --reuse-values\n\n# Rollback and reconfigure\nhelm rollback <release-name> <revision> -f values.yaml\n```\n\n### Error Reporting\n\n**Custom error messages in templates:**\n```yaml\n{{- if not .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\n{{- fail \"Controller Manager must be enabled for AgentCube to function\" }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{- if lt .Values.router.replicaCount 1 }}\n{{- fail \"Router replica count must be at least 1\" }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{- if not (hasKey .Values.controllerManager.image \"tag\") }}\n{{- fail \"Controller Manager image tag is required\" }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**Template Testing:**\n\n```yaml\n# tests/controller-manager_test.yaml\nsuite: controller manager deployment test\ntemplates:\n  - templates/controller-manager/deployment.yaml\ntests:\n  - it: should render deployment\n    asserts:\n      - isKind:\n          of: Deployment\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.name\n          value: agentcube\n  - it: should set correct replicas\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.replicas\n          value: 2\n  - it: should set correct image\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].image\n          value: agentcube/controller-manager:v1.0.0\n  - it: should set correct resource limits\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.limits.cpu\n          value: 500m\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.limits.memory\n          value: 512Mi\n  - it: should set security context\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: spec.template.spec.securityContext.runAsNonRoot\n          value: true\n  - it: should disable deployment when disabled\n    set:\n      controllerManager.enabled: false\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 0\n```\n\n**Values Testing:**\n\n```yaml\n# tests/values_test.yaml\nsuite: values validation\ntests:\n  - it: should require valid replica count\n    set:\n      controllerManager.replicaCount: -1\n    asserts:\n      - failedTemplate:\n          errorMessage: \"Replica count must be non-negative\"\n  - it: should require valid port\n    set:\n      controllerManager.service.port: 70000\n    asserts:\n      - failedTemplate:\n          errorMessage: \"Port must be between 1 and 65535\"\n```\n\n**Helper Template Testing:**\n\n```yaml\n# tests/helpers_test.yaml\nsuite: helper templates\ntemplates:\n  - templates/_helpers.tpl\ntests:\n  - it: should generate correct full name\n    asserts:\n      - matchRegex:\n          path: agentcube.fullname\n          pattern: \"^agentcube-.*\"\n  - it: should generate correct labels\n    asserts:\n      - contains:\n          path: agentcube.labels\n          content: app.kubernetes.io/name\n      - contains:\n          path: agentcube.labels\n          content: helm.sh/chart\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**Installation Test:**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# test/integration/install_test.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"Testing Helm Chart Installation...\"\n\n# Create namespace\nkubectl create namespace agentcube-test --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n\n# Install chart\nhelm install agentcube-test ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-test \\\n  --values values-test.yaml \\\n  --wait --timeout 5m\n\n# Verify deployments\nkubectl rollout status deployment/agentcube-test -n agentcube-test\nkubectl rollout status deployment/agentcube-test-workload-manager -n agentcube-test\nkubectl rollout status deployment/agentcube-test-router -n agentcube-test\n\n# Verify services\nkubectl get svc -n agentcube-test\nkubectl get endpoints -n agentcube-test\n\n# Verify pods are running\nkubectl get pods -n agentcube-test -l app.kubernetes.io/name=agentcube\n\necho \"Installation test passed!\"\n```\n\n**Upgrade Test:**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# test/integration/upgrade_test.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"Testing Helm Chart Upgrade...\"\n\n# Initial installation\nhelm install agentcube-upgrade ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-upgrade \\\n  --values values-test.yaml \\\n  --set controllerManager.replicaCount=2\n\n# Upgrade with new values\nhelm upgrade agentcube-upgrade ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-upgrade \\\n  --values values-test.yaml \\\n  --set controllerManager.replicaCount=3 \\\n  --reuse-values\n\n# Verify upgrade\nkubectl rollout status deployment/agentcube-upgrade -n agentcube-upgrade\n\n# Check replica count\nREPLICAS=$(kubectl get deployment agentcube-upgrade -n agentcube-upgrade -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}')\nif [ \"$REPLICAS\" != \"3\" ]; then\n  echo \"Upgrade test failed: expected 3 replicas, got $REPLICAS\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"Upgrade test passed!\"\n```\n\n**Rollback Test:**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# test/integration/rollback_test.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"Testing Helm Chart Rollback...\"\n\n# Install and upgrade\nhelm install agentcube-rollback ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-rollback \\\n  --values values-test.yaml \\\n  --set controllerManager.replicaCount=2\n\nhelm upgrade agentcube-rollback ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-rollback \\\n  --values values-test.yaml \\\n  --set controllerManager.replicaCount=3 \\\n  --reuse-values\n\n# Rollback\nhelm rollback agentcube-rollback 0 -n agentcube-rollback\n\n# Verify rollback\nREPLICAS=$(kubectl get deployment agentcube-rollback -n agentcube-rollback -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}')\nif [ \"$REPLICAS\" != \"2\" ]; then\n  echo \"Rollback test failed: expected 2 replicas, got $REPLICAS\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"Rollback test passed!\"\n```\n\n### E2E Tests\n\n**Functional Test:**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# test/e2e/functional_test.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"Running E2E Functional Tests...\"\n\n# Install chart\nhelm install agentcube-e2e ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-e2e \\\n  --values values-test.yaml \\\n  --wait\n\n# Test CRD creation\nkubectl apply -f ../config/samples/runtime_v1alpha1_agentruntime.yaml\n\n# Wait for resource reconciliation\nsleep 10\n\n# Verify AgentRuntime status\nSTATUS=$(kubectl get agentruntime example-runtime -n default -o jsonpath='{.status.conditions[0].status}')\nif [ \"$STATUS\" != \"True\" ]; then\n  echo \"Functional test failed: AgentRuntime not ready\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\n# Test endpoint connectivity\nSERVICE_IP=$(kubectl get svc agentcube-e2e-router -n agentcube-e2e -o jsonpath='{.spec.clusterIP}')\ncurl -f http://$SERVICE_IP:8080/healthz || exit 1\n\necho \"E2E Functional test passed!\"\n```\n\n**Environment Test:**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# test/e2e/environment_test.sh\n\necho \"Testing Multiple Environments...\"\n\n# Test development environment\nhelm install agentcube-dev ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-dev \\\n  -f values-dev.yaml\n\n# Test production environment\nhelm install agentcube-prod ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-prod \\\n  -f values-prod.yaml\n\n# Verify configurations\nDEV_REPLICAS=$(kubectl get deployment agentcube-dev -n agentcube-dev -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}')\nPROD_REPLICAS=$(kubectl get deployment agentcube-prod -n agentcube-prod -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}')\n\nif [ \"$DEV_REPLICAS\" != \"1\" ]; then\n  echo \"Dev environment test failed\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\nif [ \"$PROD_REPLICAS\" != \"3\" ]; then\n  echo \"Prod environment test failed\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"Environment test passed!\"\n```\n\n**Failure Test:**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# test/e2e/failure_test.sh\n\necho \"Testing Failure Scenarios...\"\n\n# Test with invalid values\nhelm install agentcube-fail ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-fail \\\n  --set controllerManager.replicaCount=-1 \\\n  --wait 2>&1 | grep -q \"Replica count must be non-negative\" || exit 1\n\n# Test with missing required field\nhelm install agentcube-fail2 ./agentcube \\\n  --namespace agentcube-fail2 \\\n  --set controllerManager.image.tag=\"\" \\\n  --wait 2>&1 | grep -q \"Image tag cannot be empty\" || exit 1\n\necho \"Failure test passed!\"\n```\n\n### Manual Testing Checklist\n\n**Pre-Installation:**\n- [ ] Chart.yaml has correct metadata\n- [ ] values.yaml has all required fields with defaults\n- [ ] values-dev.yaml and values-prod.yaml exist\n- [ ] All templates are valid YAML\n- [ ] CRDs are properly formatted\n- [ ] README.md is complete and accurate\n\n**Installation:**\n- [ ] `helm lint` passes\n- [ ] `helm template` renders successfully\n- [ ] `helm install` completes without errors\n- [ ] All pods are running and ready\n- [ ] All services are created\n- [ ] CRDs are installed\n- [ ] RBAC rules are applied\n\n**Post-Installation:**\n- [ ] Controller Manager is reconciling CRDs\n- [ ] Workload Manager is managing pods\n- [ ] Router is routing traffic\n- [ ] Health checks pass\n- [ ] Metrics are exposed\n- [ ] Logs are accessible\n- [ ] Network policies are applied\n\n**Upgrade:**\n- [ ] `helm upgrade` completes without errors\n- [ ] No pod disruptions\n- [ ] Configuration changes apply correctly\n- [ ] Zero downtime (if configured)\n- [ ] Previous resources are cleaned up\n\n**Rollback:**\n- [ ] `helm rollback` completes without errors\n- [ ] Configuration reverts correctly\n- [ ] Resources are restored\n- [ ] No data loss\n\n**Uninstallation:**\n- [ ] `helm uninstall` completes without errors\n- [ ] All resources are removed\n- [ ] CRDs are preserved (by default)\n- [ ] Finalizers are removed\n- [ ] No orphaned resources\n\n### CI/CD Integration\n\n**GitHub Actions Example:**\n\n```yaml\nname: Helm Chart CI\n\non:\n  push:\n    paths:\n      - 'manifests/charts/agentcube/**'\n  pull_request:\n    paths:\n      - 'manifests/charts/agentcube/**'\n\njobs:\n  lint:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Helm\n        uses: azure/setup-helm@v3\n      - name: Lint Helm Chart\n        run: |\n          helm lint manifests/charts/agentcube\n          helm template agentcube manifests/charts/agentcube --debug\n\n  test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Helm\n        uses: azure/setup-helm@v3\n      - name: Run Helm Chart Tests\n        run: |\n          cd manifests/charts/agentcube\n          helm unittest .\n```\n\n**GitLab CI Example:**\n\n```yaml\nstages:\n  - lint\n  - test\n  - deploy\n\nlint-helm:\n  stage: lint\n  image:\n    name: alpine/helm:3.12.0\n    entrypoint: [\"\"]\n  script:\n    - helm lint manifests/charts/agentcube\n    - helm template agentcube manifests/charts/agentcube --debug\n\ntest-helm:\n  stage: test\n  image:\n    name: alpine/helm:3.12.0\n    entrypoint: [\"\"]\n  script:\n    - apk add --no-cache go\n    - go install github.com/quintush/helm-unittest@latest\n    - helm unittest manifests/charts/agentcube\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| Kubernetes | 1.20+ | Container orchestration platform |\n| Helm | 3.0+ | Package manager |\n| Prometheus Operator | 0.50+ (optional) | ServiceMonitor support |\n\n### Development Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| helm | 3.12.0+ | Helm CLI |\n| helm-unittest | 0.3.x | Helm template testing |\n| kubectl | 1.27+ | Kubernetes CLI |\n| yamllint | 1.33+ | YAML linting |\n| kubeconform | 0.6+ | Kubernetes manifest validation |\n\n### Build Tools\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `helm lint` | Validate chart syntax and structure |\n| `helm template` | Render templates without installing |\n| `helm package` | Package chart for distribution |\n| `helm repo index` | Generate repository index |\n\n## Documentation\n\n### README.md Structure\n\n```markdown\n# AgentCube Helm Chart\n\nKubernetes-native AI agent runtime and code interpreter platform.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Kubernetes 1.20+\n- Helm 3.0+\n- (Optional) Prometheus Operator\n\n## Installation\n\n### Default Installation\n\n```bash\nhelm repo add agentcube https://charts.agentcube.io\nhelm install agentcube agentcube/agentcube\n```\n\n### Custom Values\n\n```bash\nhelm install agentcube agentcube/agentcube \\\n  --set controllerManager.replicaCount=3 \\\n  --set router.ingress.enabled=true\n```\n\n### Environment-Specific\n\n```bash\n# Development\nhelm install agentcube agentcube/agentcube -f values-dev.yaml\n\n# Production\nhelm install agentcube agentcube/agentcube -f values-prod.yaml\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\nSee [values.yaml](values.yaml) for all configuration options.\n\n### Key Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Description | Default |\n|-----------|-------------|---------|\n| `controllerManager.enabled` | Enable Controller Manager | `true` |\n| `controllerManager.replicaCount` | Number of replicas | `2` |\n| `workloadManager.enabled` | Enable Workload Manager | `true` |\n| `workloadManager.replicaCount` | Number of replicas | `2` |\n| `router.enabled` | Enable Router | `true` |\n| `router.replicaCount` | Number of replicas | `3` |\n| `monitoring.enabled` | Enable monitoring | `false` |\n| `rbac.create` | Create RBAC resources | `true` |\n\n## Upgrading\n\n```bash\nhelm upgrade agentcube agentcube/agentcube\n```\n\n## Uninstalling\n\n```bash\nhelm uninstall agentcube\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Pods not starting\n\nCheck logs:\n```bash\nkubectl logs -n agentcube -l app.kubernetes.io/name=agentcube\n```\n\n### Installation fails\n\nRun with debug:\n```bash\nhelm install agentcube agentcube/agentcube --debug\n```\n\n## Contributing\n\nSee [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md)\n\n## License\n\nApache License 2.0\n```\n\n### Values.yaml Documentation\n\n```yaml\n# Global Configuration\n# ===================\nglobal:\n  # Image registry for all images\n  # Type: string\n  # Default: \"\"\n  imageRegistry: \"\"\n\n  # Image pull secrets\n  # Type: array\n  # Default: []\n  imagePullSecrets: []\n\n  # Override the namespace\n  # Type: string\n  # Default: \"agentcube\"\n  namespaceOverride: \"\"\n\n# Controller Manager Configuration\n# ================================\ncontrollerManager:\n  # Enable controller manager\n  # Type: boolean\n  # Default: true\n  enabled: true\n\n  # Number of replicas\n  # Type: integer\n  # Default: 2\n  replicaCount: 2\n\n  # Image configuration\n  image:\n    # Image repository\n    # Type: string\n    # Default: \"agentcube/controller-manager\"\n    repository: agentcube/controller-manager\n\n    # Image tag\n    # Type: string\n    # Default: \"\" (uses Chart appVersion)\n    tag: \"\"\n\n    # Image pull policy\n    # Type: string\n    # Options: Always, IfNotPresent, Never\n    # Default: IfNotPresent\n    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n\n  # Service configuration\n  service:\n    # Service type\n    # Type: string\n    # Options: ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer\n    # Default: ClusterIP\n    type: ClusterIP\n\n    # Service port\n    # Type: integer\n    # Range: 1-65535\n    # Default: 8080\n    port: 8080\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### RBAC Best Practices\n\n1. **Least Privilege**: Grant only necessary permissions\n2. **Service Accounts**: Use dedicated service accounts per component\n3. **Role Separation**: Separate roles for different components\n4. **No ClusterAdmin**: Avoid using cluster-admin when possible\n\n### Secrets Management\n\n1. **External Secrets**: Prefer external secret management (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager)\n2. **Kubernetes Secrets**: Use encrypted etcd for secrets\n3. **Values File**: Never commit secrets in values.yaml\n4. **Secret Encryption**: Enable Secret encryption at rest\n\n### Network Security\n\n1. **Network Policies**: Default deny all, allow specific traffic\n2. **Service Types**: Use ClusterIP internally, limit LoadBalancer exposure\n3. **TLS/HTTPS**: Enable TLS for external endpoints\n4. **Ingress Validation**: Validate ingress configuration\n\n### Container Security\n\n1. **Non-root**: Run containers as non-root user\n2. **Read-only**: Use read-only root filesystem\n3. **Capabilities**: Drop all capabilities\n4. **Security Context**: Configure pod and container security contexts\n\n### Image Security\n\n1. **Signed Images**: Use signed container images\n2. **Private Registry**: Use private registries with authentication\n3. **Vulnerability Scanning**: Scan images before deployment\n4. **Base Images**: Use minimal base images\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Resource Allocation\n\n**Default Resource Requests:**\n\n| Component | CPU Request | Memory Request | CPU Limit | Memory Limit |\n|-----------|-------------|----------------|-----------|--------------|\n| Controller Manager | 100m | 128Mi | 500m | 512Mi |\n| Workload Manager | 200m | 256Mi | 1000m | 1Gi |\n| Router | 150m | 192Mi | 750m | 768Mi |\n\n### Horizontal Pod Autoscaling\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  autoscaling:\n    enabled: true\n    minReplicas: 2\n    maxReplicas: 5\n    targetCPUUtilizationPercentage: 80\n    targetMemoryUtilizationPercentage: 80\n```\n\n### High Availability\n\n1. **Multi-replica**: Deploy multiple replicas\n2. **Pod Anti-Affinity**: Spread pods across nodes\n3. **Pod Disruption Budget**: Prevent disruptions during maintenance\n4. **Health Checks**: Configure liveness and readiness probes\n\n### Caching and Optimization\n\n1. **Image Layers**: Optimize Docker image layers\n2. **Pull Policy**: Use IfNotPresent pull policy\n3. **Resource Limits**: Set appropriate limits to prevent resource contention\n4. **Affinity Rules**: Use node affinity for better locality\n\n## Migration Strategy\n\n### From Manual YAML to Helm\n\n1. **Extract Configuration**: Convert existing YAML configurations to values.yaml\n2. **Test Chart**: Deploy chart in test environment\n3. **Validate Functionality**: Ensure all features work correctly\n4. **Rollout**: Gradually roll out to production\n5. **Cleanup**: Remove manual YAML after verification\n\n### Version Migration\n\n1. **Backup**: Backup current installation\n2. **Test Upgrade**: Test upgrade in non-production\n3. **Rollout**: Upgrade production cluster\n4. **Monitor**: Monitor for issues\n5. **Rollback**: Have rollback plan ready\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Helm chart installs successfully on Kubernetes 1.20+\n- All components start and are healthy\n- CRDs are properly installed and functional\n- Configuration through values.yaml works correctly\n- Multi-environment deployment (dev/test/prod) supported\n- Installation, upgrade, and rollback workflows tested\n- All unit and integration tests pass\n- Security best practices followed\n- Documentation complete and accurate\n- Performance benchmarks met\n- Zero downtime upgrades (when configured)\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Additional Components**: Add support for additional AgentCube components\n2. **Backup/Restore**: Integrated backup and restore functionality\n3. **Multi-cluster**: Support for multi-cluster deployments\n4. **Service Mesh**: Istio and Linkerd integration\n5. **Advanced Monitoring**: Grafana dashboards and alerting rules\n6. **Custom Resources**: Additional custom resources and operators\n7. **GitOps**: ArgoCD and Flux integration examples\n8. **Validation**: Values validation schema and tools","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/config/samples/runtime_v1alpha1_agentruntime.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","time":{"start":1775881038858,"end":1775881038869}}}}
